{{fr-noun|m}}

# [[zero]], [[nought]], [[oh]] {{q|in reading numbers}}
# {{lb|fr|value}} [[zero]], [[nought]]
# {{lb|fr|colloquial}} a [[zero]], a [[person]] of [[very]] [[poor]] [[value]]

====Usage notes====
* Whereas in English the [[Appendix:Glossary#singular|singular]] is used only after the number [[one]], in French it is typically used after numbers ''smaller than [[two]]''. This means that both ''zéro'' and {{m|fr|un}} are generally used with the singular, even when they are followed by a [[decimal]] part.

:: {{uxi|fr|zéro '''point'''|zero points}}
:: {{uxi|fr|0,35 '''mètre'''|0.35 metres}}
:: {{uxi|fr|1,99 '''euro'''|1.99 euros}}

